INSERT INTO `events` VALUES (1,'Ganapathi Navaratri','Tarpanams, Abhishekam, Archana, Yantra Puja and Anna danam','2016-09-05','2016-09-13',''),(3,'Amrita Kaumudi','','2016-09-26','2016-09-28','https://c2.staticflickr.com/9/8362/28486887153_940cdd421b.jpg'),(4,'Anandam','<div class=\"container-fluid eventbody\">\n    <div class=\"row\">\n		<div class=\"col-md-12\">\n			<br />\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"row marr\">\n		<div class=\"col-md-3 marr0\">\n			\n			<img src=\"/images/3.jpg\" class=\"img-responsive\" />		</div>\n		<div class=\"col-md-9 marr1\">\n\n				<div class=\"transbox\">\n					<p>Anandam has its root in the Sanskrit word Ananda which means Happiness. It is one of the 3 liberating attributes of the Atman, the other two being Truth and Consciousness- Sat-Chit-Ananda. It is the realm of Bliss experienced when one transcends from the drama of life to the essence of Truth. </p>\n\n					<p><b>Anandam</b> is a Spiritual Retreat organized by Devipuram to provide you with the joyful experience of Sri Vidya- the Ancient Spiritual Science which enables you to unleash your full potential.</p>\n\n					<p>While there are elaborate rituals and deep contemplations that are involved in the study of this science, this Retreat is an genuine Experience of Sri Vidya, which is nothing but Happiness in practice. </p>\n\n					<p>In your journey to <b>Anandam</b> you will have the opportunity to go beyond the limitations of time. Activities include group Music & Dance sessions that enable you to let go of your inhibitions and learn to laugh like children again; Kundalini Meditation and Yoganidra that enhance your knowledge on the Chakras and channelize your inner energy; empowerment rituals which activate the subtle senses in your body providing you with the deep meditative experience of <b>being</b> the Goddess. </p>\n\n					<p>Observe nature through sunrise walks, gaze at the hues of sunset, space out your thoughts, and reflect in silence. Be part of a collective cocoon, where each one of us shares our reflections and together we arrive at a better understanding of the Self. </p>\n\n					<p>Here is your opportunity to witness and participate in the awakening of your senses. The picturesque hills of Devipuram welcome you all into the embrace of Her arms and nurturing space of her womb, to share your collective wisdom; to enjoy the differences that bring us together and to learn from our varied perspectives. </p>\n\n					<p>Anandam at Devipuram is a universe by itself..Come tune into the harmony..</p>\n				</div>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n\n	<div class=\"row\">\n		<div class=\"col-md-12 marr1\">\n			<div class=\"background\">\n				<div class=\"transbox\">\n					<h3>Further details : </h4>\n					<p>The retreat is being organized at Devipuram. Sri Vidya practitioners will be at hand to guide the process. Participants will be provided with comfortable single accommodation to facilitate a relaxing stay, and meals will be sattvic and vegetarian.  The schedule will be fluid and managed to ensure that the participants have a rejuvenating experience.</p>\n\n					<p>We will be commencing post lunch on the 27th December. Please plan to arrive by 11 am on the 27th. Departures may be planned post 6pm on the 30th. Pick up and drop facility from the airport/ railway station can be arranged on request.</p>\n\n					<h3>Pricing:</h3>\n					<p>The retreat is being offered at an introductory price. The price is inclusive of food and accommodation (single Non-AC rooms). Rooms with air-conditioning are also available, at an extra charge.</p>\n\n					<h3>For Indian nationals:  Rs.9,000 per person </h3>\n\n					<h3>For Foreign nationals- USD 150 per person </h3>\n\n					<h2>Register for the retreat:</h2>\n\n					<h4>Write in to info@devipuram.com with Anandam in the subject line.</h4>\n\n					<p>Devipuram is 35 km from Visakhapatnam and is reachable by air and train. Devipuram is about 25 km from the airport, 35 km from Visakhapatnam railway station and 12 km from Anakapalle railway station. </p>\n\n					<h4>For regular updates, please visit our social media handles </h4>\n					<p>Our official facebook page: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/srividya.devipuram\" class=\"aa\">www.facebook.com/srividya.devipuram</a></p>\n					<p>Youtube channel: <a href=\"https://www.Youtube.com/devipuram1\" class=\"aa\">Youtube.com/devipuram1</a> </p>\n					<p>Twitter: <a href=\"https://www.twitter.com/devipuram\" class=\"aa\">@devipuram</a> </p>\n					<p>Instagram: <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/devipuram1\" class=\"aa\">devipuram1</a></p>\n				</div>\n			</div>\n		</div>\n','2016-12-27','2016-12-30','http://devipuram.com/specialevents/index'),(6,'NewEventTitle','NewEventDescription','2017-07-20','2017-07-27','NewEventImageUrl'),(7,'event2','eventdis2','2017-07-22','2017-07-27','eventimageurl2'),(8,'event3','eventdis3','2017-07-22','2017-07-27','eventimageurl3'),(10,'event4','eventdis4','2017-07-22','2017-07-27','eventimageurl4'),(11,'event5','eventdis5','2017-07-25','2017-07-27','eventimgurl5'),(12,'event6','eventdis6','2017-07-25','2017-07-27','eventimageurl6'),(13,'event7','eventdis7','2017-07-25','2017-07-28','eventimageurl7'),(14,'event8','eventdis78','2017-07-25','2017-07-28','eventimageurl8'),(15,'event9','eventdis9','2017-08-02','2017-08-05','Event ImageUrl');
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `events` ENABLE KEYS */;
